80","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Middlesex, England, United Kingdom":"Middlesex, England, United Kingdom","Stepney, London, England":"Stepney, London, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Marrow","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: nickname from Middle English <i>marwe</i>, <i>marowe</i> ‘companion, mate’."],"variants":[{"name":"Marra","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Antonio, Rocco, Carmine, Salvatore, Enrico, Pasquale, Sal, Vincenzo, Alessandro, Gaetano, Marino.","Italian (southern): habitational name from any of the places so called in central and southern Italy, from <i>marra</i> ‘heap of stones’.","Italian, Galician, and Portuguese: from <i>marra</i> ‘hoe’, in Galician and Portuguese also ‘big mallet for breaking stones’ (from Latin <i>marra</i>), presumably a metonymic occupational name for one who made such implements or for one who used them."]},{"name":"Merrow","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Marrow  .","English: habitational name from Merrow in Surrey, apparently derived from Old English <i>mearg</i> ‘marrow, fat’, used figuratively to mean ‘fertile ground’.","Americanized form of French   Amirault   or of any of its altered forms. Compare   Meraw   and   Mero   4."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir William Marrow II was born about 1354, in Stepney, London, England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir William Marrow I, was 30 and his mother, Lady Catherine Rich, was 25. He had at least 1 son with Margaret Ryche. He died in 1450, in Middlesex, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 97."},"et":{"about 1354–1450":"umbes 1354–1450","1354–1450":"1354–1450","1358–Female":"1358–Surnud","1354–Female":"1354–Surnud","1380–1450":"1380–1450","1325–Male":"1325–Surnud","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","1325":"1325","1358":"1358","1354":"1354","1330":"1330","1450":"1450","about 1354":"umbes 1354","1380":"1380","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Middlesex, England, United Kingdom":"Middlesex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stepney, London, England":"Stepney, London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1354–1450":"noin 1354–1450","1354–1450":"1354–1450","1358–Female":"1358–Kuollut","1354–Female":"1354–Kuollut","1380–1450":"1380–1450","1325–Male":"1325–Kuollut","1330–Female":"1330–Kuollut","1325":"1325","1358":"1358","1354":"1354","1330":"1330","1450":"1450","about 1354":"noin 1354","1380":"1380","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Middlesex, England, United Kingdom":"Middlesex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Stepney, London, England":"Stepney, London, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1354–1450":"environ 1354–1450","1354–1450":"1354–1450","1358–Female":"1358–Décédée","1354–Female":"1354–Décédée","1380–1450":"1380–1450","1325–Male":"1325–Décédé","1330–Female":"1330–Décédée","1325":"1325","1358":"1358","1354":"1354","1330":"1330","1450":"1450","about 1354":"environ 1354","1380":"1380","London, Middlesex, England":"Londres, Middlesex, Angleterre","Middlesex, England, United Kingdom":"Middlesex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Stepney, London, England":"Stepney, Londr